  "text": "Found all 5 key ASan implementation files across both compilers:\n\n1. **LLVM compiler-rt interceptors** (`compiler-rt/lib/asan/asan_interceptors.cpp`): Intercepts libc functions (pthread_create, longjmp, mmap, etc.) via the `INTERCEPTOR` macro. Primary function: `InitializeAsanInterceptors()` (line 900).\n\n2. **LLVM compiler-rt runtime init** (`compiler-rt/lib/asan/asan_rtl.cpp`): Implements ASan runtime initialization. Entry point `__asan_init()` (line 678) calls `AsanInitFromRtl()` which calls `AsanInitInternal()` (line 426) \u2014 the core init logic that sets up flags, shadow memory, interceptors, and allocator.\n\n3. **LLVM IR instrumentation pass** (`llvm/lib/Transforms/Instrumentation/AddressSanitizer.cpp`): Contains `AddressSanitizerPass` (the new-PM pass, line 1295), `struct AddressSanitizer` (per-function instrumentation, line 775), and `class ModuleAddressSanitizer` (module-level instrumentation for globals, line 929).\n\n4. **GCC ASan implementation** (`gcc/asan.cc`): Contains `class pass_asan` (line 4468, a `gimple_opt_pass`) whose `execute()` calls `asan_instrument()` (line 4431). Also contains `asan_expand_check_ifn()` for expanding sanitizer checks and `asan_emit_stack_protection()` for stack instrumentation.\n\n5. **GCC ASan header** (`gcc/asan.h`): Declares the public ASan API including `asan_emit_stack_protection`, `asan_expand_check_ifn`, `asan_protect_global`, `asan_finish_file`, and related HWASan functions.",
